# Trivy Ignore File — Suppress false-positive vulnerability findings
# Each entry must include the vulnerability ID and a justification.
# Review periodically (quarterly) to check if Trivy's DB has been updated.

# CVE-2026-1260 (GHSA-38vq-g6vr-w8wf) — sentencepiece heap overflow
# Affects: sentencepiece < 0.2.1
# Status: FIXED in sentencepiece==0.2.1 (which we pin in requirements.txt)
# The v0.2.1 release notes explicitly state "Security fix to address a heap overflow issue".
# Trivy's vulnerability database may not yet reflect that 0.2.1 is the patched version.
# This is a confirmed false positive — our pinned version IS the fix.
CVE-2026-1260

# CVE-2025-69872 — diskcache 5.6.3 arbitrary code execution via crafted cache file
# Affects: diskcache == 5.6.3 (ALL available versions — no upstream fix released yet)
# Attack vector: LOCAL — attacker must have write access to the cache directory.
# Mitigation: cache directory restricted to service user (chmod 700).
# Review: check quarterly for upstream fix; update requirements.txt when released.
# Added: 2026-05
CVE-2025-69872
